column21: When we came in, our bathroom smelled terrible.   Also the floor was not very clean.  Some of the dishes in the kitchen were not clean - the first bowl I took out for my cereal, for instance, as well as a couple of the knives in the cutlery drawer.  Also a cup was cracked so when one of my companions put milk into it, the milk poured out the bottom.
column23: This is a tight-space college apartment,  plain and simple.  If you`re looking for a place to park your stuff and then be outside in the city all day, just come back to sleep, it`s great.  The beds, pillows and linens are wonderfully comfortable, showers are fine, sinks outside the shower area is a convenient arrangement.  But the common space is tiny, especially if there are 6 of you for the whole apartment as there were in my group; also, there are only two small windows, one each in each room, so it`s not very inviting to hang out in.   Parking is easy - there`s a parking lot right on the next street or you can look for street parking, some of it metered some of it free.  Also a convenience store open 24 hours across the street.  It seemed to be a business area, kind of empty, also with a pawn-shop-type of place on the corner that was a little shady. But it didn`t feel unsafe.  We did have to drive to all the stuff we wanted to go to, like the Warhol museum, restaurants in the main cultural center, but it`
column25: The host was very responsive to begin with, but did not respond to a complaint about a smelling bathroom.  As it turned out, the bathroom was fine after we left the door open for a while, but we didn`t know that when I sent the email.
column31: It was kind of shady, with a pawn shop practically next door.  I didn`t feel unsafe but it wasn`t as hopping center-of-town as I`d expected.
column34: My main suggestions would be to ensure the floors are cleaner, the rooms not smelling, and the kitchenware clean.  Keep beds and linens as is - they were really comfortable.

column23: Z & C are providing a vital, affordable service to people visiting Pittsburgh. They manage several units, 2 of which I have stayed in - spotless. I would instantly book with them again.Z & C are chasing the dream. Instead of allowing these skyscrapers to sit vacant as ghost houses, they have undertaken the visionary effort to restore and squeeze revenue out of the steel giants. What a great idea, you might say, to get the plumbing and fire alarms working again, and manage two dozen rotating tenants and a cleaning crew - it is easier said than done, and Z & C are growing rapidly towards sustainability.Bravo - here`s to the rebirth of the Steel City.
column34: I am interested in sending you two a modest endowment. You are entrepreneurs driving sustainable economic growth in the region. Not to mention, it is a shame for those buildings to sit empty - you are squeezing revenue out of them in a valuable, creative way.I would not ask anything in return for my gift. You are welcome to invest in the business, or to withdraw the money and treat yourselves to a nice weekend away. I can offer $500 - not going to make or break you... probably just an extra day`s revenue if all units were filled, I would imagine.Please let me know if you can accept my offer. If you wish to discuss further, message me here, email nate@mykolab.com, or call/text 734-395-0249.Sincerely,Nate ShiffOberlin OH Formerly Pgh

column23: The price and location are fantastic and I would definitely recommend staying here.  It was clean, convenient, spacious, and a great bargain for a nice place.Some tips:-Zach will send you a code for keys, and I would recommend double checking the code with him prior to arrival.  The code he gave me in a generic auto-response was incorrect, and it was a bit scary to try to check in and have the lock box not work.  (It was resolved quickly over text, but this seemed like an important detail to get wrong).-I also wrote to Zach and Casey with a few specific questions, and received mostly generic auto-responses.  To be fair, I booked last minute so maybe if you write to them early on you’ll get more personalized responses.-The bed closest to the wall is more more comfortable.  The mattress near the windows felt worn out and sunken in.Overall I was happy with this Airbnb, especially for the price and the convenience.  If you’re interested in a professional, hands off, experience with minimal interaction with the ho
column34: Thanks so much for hosting, the price and the location were perfect.I was disappointed to receive the wrong check in info at first - arriving at a new place, at night, as a solo female traveler,  in the snow, it made me nervous when the lockbox code you provided was incorrect and you didn’t pick up the phone when I called.  I really appreciated the quick text response, but would have preferred a little more genuine communication from the start rather than generic correspondence that was inaccurate and didn’t answer all of my questions.This is totally not required, but it would have made me feel more safe to get info from you about the other room. column23: I came to Pittsburgh with my brother for the PGH half marathon / marathon and this place was exactly what we were looking for. We were less than a 10 min walk from the start and finish lines and a 15 min walk from PNC park for a Pirates game afterwards. The space is small and simple, but our beds were comfortable, the shower was hot and the towels were soft. Maybe the whole place was full of other runners, but I didn’t hear any noise from neighbors. column23: This place looks great online but beware. The building is terrifying upon entrance as a woman. Once you actually get in the “apartment” it’s fine, but the hallways and elevators scream unsafe. Cleaning staff was beyond friendly and helpful. They were great. The space is decorated nice but it’s basically a dorm space with a very small kitchenette and living area. The host is EXTREMELY unresponsive. I had to ask for check in materials several times before getting a response and even then I was told I would get it by 3pm the next day, and did not receive them until 9am the morning of check in. He was quick to send us check out materials though. There were some spaces in the kitchen (and probably other areas too) where holes were cut in the ceiling for what looked like a sprinkler system. They just left a gaping hole around the head though which just looked awful. Overall, I think this place is overpriced by about 100 bucks and they need a new host or make it clear this one needs to learn how to respond.

column23: I visited Pittsburgh for a music festival and I ended up booking with Zachary three days prior to my trip, as my original host cancelled last minute. The unit itself (which is a bit bigger in person than it appears in photos) had everything I needed for my short stay! In addition, the location was amazing, conveniently placed in a quiet nook of downtown within walking distance of many of the places I`d planned to visit (including the fest). A few comments: although there is AC, there is no thermostat in the unit (or at least not one I could find) and therefore you have no control over the internal temperature (however, it did stay fairly comfortable during my stay). I only slept on one of the twin beds; the mattress was not the most comfortable mattress I`ve slept on, but it was acceptable, and the bed linens were quiet nice. The couch was extremely comfortable as well! The TV had horrible reception, but this was not a major issue as I simply used my laptop to stream entertainment. Also, as mentioned in other
column25: I reached out with several inquiries prior to and during the course of my stay; I had to follow up several times and ultimately did not receive answers to a few of my questions. When another guest as throwing a party, I contacted Zachary in the hopes it would be resolved, however I did not receive a response until the next morning after I had to follow up on another issue. As someone who truly appreciates responsiveness and good communication with her hosts, this was very upsetting to say the least.
column34: Hi Zacahry; thank you for my stay. The location was great and the unit had everything I needed. I would suggest in the future you make a stronger effort to read and respond to messages from your guests; I felt like many of the messages I sent you were never addressed and this is very frustrating. Also, I would recommend fixing or simply removing the broken tile in the bathroom area. Apart from that, I had a very enjoyable stay.
